Preparation of the reagents:

                              1)

Standard solutions of MnCl2 or CoCl2 in water at concentration ranging from 0.01μM to 1mM were prepared from the corresponding stock solutions (2mM);


                              2)

20mM Tris-sulfate buffer (TB) at different pH values: from 6.5 to 10.5;


                              3)

Stock solutions of 100mM Arg in 30mM TB at different pH values: from 6.5 to 10.5;


                              4)

Freshly prepared chemical reagent for urea (for 10 assays): mixture of 18mL 0.5% aqueous solution of DMO and 12mL 3M H2SO4.
